<p>Sometimes it’s nice to take a break from endlessly scrolling through your feed — and endlessly scroll through someone’s individual Instagram page instead.</p>
<p>Welcome to The Grid.</p>
<p>Lined up in neat rows of three, each Instagram post suddenly is part of a bigger picture. A peek into a user’s soul… or at least their <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/instagram-marketing/">content strategy</a>.</p>
<p>And Instagram power users know just how to work this viewpoint to their advantage with artfully planned posts that, together, create a gorgeous Instagram grid layout.</p>
<p>If you haven’t thought about what your own rows of squares add up to, it’s about time. Here’s all you need to know about building an attention-grabbing Instagram grid to grow your following and <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/instagram-engagement/">engagement</a>. 					</p><div class="
						content-upgrade _bonusVariantContentUpgrade
						style-default											" style="
															">

											<a href="https://www.hootsuite.com/resources/blog/instagram-post-templates" class="cover" data-ga-track-id="blog_contentupgrade_inpost_gate" target="_blank"></a>
											<div class="all-content-wrapper">
														<div class="text-wrapper">
																<p><strong>Bonus:</strong> Claim your <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>free pack of 15 creative Instagram post templates</strong></span> made by Hootsuite’s professional graphic designers. Easily customize them in Canva, and start getting more engagement today.</p>
															</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				
<h2><a id="post-400341-_pfa26iljj5h2"></a><strong>Why your Instagram grid layout matters</strong></h2>
<p>When someone follows you for the first time or navigates to your profile to check out your content, your Instagram photo grid is an opportunity to showcase your vibe or brand at a glance.</p>
<p>The grid gives you a birds-eye view of a user’s posting history. This is your first impression of their body of work: a visual, big-picture introduction to their personal or professional brand.</p>
<p>For individual users, creating a beautiful grid may not matter — sure, color coding your posts could be a fun personal challenge, but if you’re just on the ‘gram to connect with friends, not amass an audience, branding likely isn’t too important.</p>
<p>But for brands, creatives, or influencers, consistency and style are critical, particularly if your account is focused on aesthetics or lifestyle.</p>
<p>After all, your grid is a quick and easy way to get your message across. Plus, anyone viewing your profile is thinking about following you. This is your chance to show exactly what you offer.</p>
<p>Are you avant-garde or on-trend? Will your content soothe or bring the drama? Is your brand consistent or chaotic? One look at a grid, and they’ll get the (sorry, not sorry) picture.</p>
<h2><a id="post-400341-_7obpjmszhkcd"></a><strong>10 creative ways to design an Instagram grid layout</strong></h2>
<p>Great grids for Instagram start with a vision. So we’ve scoured the platform to dig up some of the best grids on Instagram to inspire your own look. Think of these as your Instagram grid templates.</p>
<h3><span id="Commit_to_a_color_combo"><a id="post-400341-_ddgxy8z86kfx"></a><strong>Commit to a color combo</strong></span></h3>
<p>This is probably the most common grid style going — not that I’m calling anyone lazy (don’t @ me!), but it really doesn’t get much easier than this.</p>
<p>Pick a color palette (pinks and greys?) or a certain tone (high contrast neons?) to feature in every photo. Viewed together, your gallery will look like a matching set, even if the content of your pics varies. Home and lifestyle influencer</p>
<p>Travel Instagrammer <a href="http://instagram.com/rachelontheroad_">@rachelontheroad_</a> exclusively features photos from a desaturated palette of cool blues, pinks, and greys. A neon green pic, for instance, would seem jarring and out of place here.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grids-01.png"><picture decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-400653">
<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grids-01-310x671.png.webp 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grids-01-620x1342.png.webp 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grids-01-768x1662.png.webp 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grids-01-710x1536.png.webp 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grids-01-946x2048.png.webp 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grids-01.png.webp 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
<img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grids-01-310x671.png" alt="Travel Instagram Rachel on the Road cool colour palette" width="310" height="671" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grids-01-310x671.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grids-01-620x1342.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grids-01-768x1662.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grids-01-710x1536.png 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grids-01-946x2048.png 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grids-01.png 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
</picture>
</a></p>
<p>In case your travel destination (or home or office) isn’t decorated like an Insta-ready backdrop, one easy way to make sure your photos all speak the same visual language is simply to use the same filter for every photo to help create a consistent tone.</p>
<p>A variation on this theme? Using a standard filter or color palette, but also working in an “accent” color or filter every few posts, too. Maybe your Instagram feed is mostly dreamy, sepia-toned boho fantasy, but every few rows, we see a vibrant pop of forest green. Woo! You’re playing with <em>fire</em>!</p>
<p>We couldn’t tell you <em>exactly </em>what <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/free-instagram-presets/">Lightroom preset</a> <a href="http://instagram.com/lemons.for.days">@lemons.for.days</a> is using but… probably something called, like, “Peach Dew Dreams.”</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-03.png"><picture decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-400637">
<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-03-310x671.png.webp 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-03-620x1342.png.webp 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-03-768x1662.png.webp 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-03-710x1536.png.webp 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-03-946x2048.png.webp 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-03.png.webp 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
<img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-03-310x671.png" alt="Lemon for Days peachy colour theme" width="310" height="671" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-03-310x671.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-03-620x1342.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-03-768x1662.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-03-710x1536.png 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-03-946x2048.png 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-03.png 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
</picture>
</a></p>
<h3><span id="Repeat_yourself"><a id="post-400341-_w72dgzoyiuhw"></a>Repeat yourself</span></h3>
<p>There’s something soothing about scrolling a feed that gives you the same thing over and over again. There’s no doubt what you’re going to get when every photo follows the same template.</p>
<p>In the case of decorative cakemaker <a href="http://instagram.com/takemehome_cake">@takemehome_cake</a>, each creation is photographed from the exact same angle on the same backdrop. The color may vary due to seasonal lighting, but the result is a pleasingly predictable feed where the individual product gets to pop against an endless grid of grey.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grid-02.png"><picture decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-400645">
<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grid-02-310x671.png.webp 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grid-02-620x1342.png.webp 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grid-02-768x1662.png.webp 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grid-02-710x1536.png.webp 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grid-02-946x2048.png.webp 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grid-02.png.webp 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
<img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grid-02-310x671.png" alt="decorative cakes instagram consistent theme" width="310" height="671" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grid-02-310x671.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grid-02-620x1342.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grid-02-768x1662.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grid-02-710x1536.png 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grid-02-946x2048.png 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Instagram-grid-02.png 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
</picture>
</a></p>
<h3><span id="Create_a_checkerboard_effect"><a id="post-400341-_rbak67c4xugy"></a><strong>Create a checkerboard effect</strong></span></h3>
<p>By alternating the style of photos you post, you’ll easily create a checkerboard look on your grid. Try alternating text quotes with photography or mixing close-up shots with landscape photos. Going back and forth with two distinct colors can work, too.</p>
<p>Influencer <a href="http://instagram.com/jillian.harris">@jillian.harris</a> alternates full-frame photos with pink-border pics to create a unique grid look.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-05.png"><picture decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-400621">
<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-05-310x671.png.webp 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-05-620x1342.png.webp 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-05-768x1662.png.webp 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-05-710x1536.png.webp 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-05-946x2048.png.webp 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-05.png.webp 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
<img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-05-310x671.png" alt="Jillian Harris pink bordered pictures" width="310" height="671" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-05-310x671.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-05-620x1342.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-05-768x1662.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-05-710x1536.png 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-05-946x2048.png 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-05.png 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
</picture>
</a></p>
<p>Food blogger <a href="http://instagram.com/feedthepudge">@feedthepudge</a> alternates food posts with ones of his own face to offer variety for anyone scrolling through.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-04.png"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-400629" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-04-310x671.png" alt="Food blogger feed the purge alternate pictures food and face" width="310" height="671" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-04-310x671.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-04-620x1342.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-04-768x1662.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-04-710x1536.png 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-04-946x2048.png 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-04.png 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"></a></p>
<p>Vancouver fitness studio <a href="http://instagram.com/cmmngrndyvr">@cmmngrndyvr</a> mixes bright graphics with dark and moody photos.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-08.jpeg"><picture decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-400605">
