</picture>
</a></p>
<p>Hot tip: if you’re using text-based posts, keep the background color or fonts consistent to really make the pattern clear. Check and mate.</p>
<p>(Need a little help on the graphic design front? There are tons of great <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/instagram-tools/">tools and templates</a> out there to create visuals that pop.)</p>
<h3><span id="Design_row_by_row"><a id="post-400341-_p40caouwaxm9"></a><strong>Design row by row</strong></span></h3>
<p>Think outside the box… and inside the, um, row. Uniting the images on each row by theme or color can create a powerful impact</p>
<p>Sorry if you’re squeamish about freshly tattooed skin, but this example from <a href="http://instagram.com/spooky_skeleton_wizard">@spooky_skeleton_wizard</a> had to be shared. This tattoo studio alternates rows of sketches with rows of new ink.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-06.png"><picture decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-400613">
<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-06-310x671.png.webp 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-06-620x1342.png.webp 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-06-768x1662.png.webp 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-06-710x1536.png.webp 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-06-946x2048.png.webp 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-06.png.webp 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
<img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-06-310x671.png" alt="spooky skeleton wizard instagram fresh tattoos and sketch examples" width="310" height="671" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-06-310x671.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-06-620x1342.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-06-768x1662.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-06-710x1536.png 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-06-946x2048.png 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-06.png 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
</picture>
</a></p>
<p>The trick for this one, of course, is that you have to post three images at a time, or the alignment will be off.</p>
<p>If you’re bold enough to experiment with panoramic images for one of your rows — a trio of photos that add up to one long, horizontal image — many users post the same caption for each one to make it clear they’re three parts of a whole, like photographer<a href="https://www.instagram.com/gregorygeipel"> @gregorygiepel </a>did with his architectural shots.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screen-Shot-2023-04-04-at-2.54.27-PM.png"><picture decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-400661">
<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screen-Shot-2023-04-04-at-2.54.27-PM-620x202.png.webp 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screen-Shot-2023-04-04-at-2.54.27-PM-310x101.png.webp 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screen-Shot-2023-04-04-at-2.54.27-PM-768x250.png.webp 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screen-Shot-2023-04-04-at-2.54.27-PM.png.webp 1160w" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px"/>
<img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screen-Shot-2023-04-04-at-2.54.27-PM-620x202.png" alt="Gregory Geipel joint architectural shots" width="620" height="202" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screen-Shot-2023-04-04-at-2.54.27-PM-620x202.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screen-Shot-2023-04-04-at-2.54.27-PM-310x101.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screen-Shot-2023-04-04-at-2.54.27-PM-768x250.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screen-Shot-2023-04-04-at-2.54.27-PM.png 1160w" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px"/>
</picture>
</a></p>
<h3><span id="Break_outside_of_the_box"><a id="post-400341-_ga6bdm4fnn8"></a>Break outside of the box</span></h3>
<p>Though the grid by nature crops all of your Instagram photos to a square, editing your photos to a different shape <em>within </em>that square can create a distinct look for your Instagram photo grid.</p>
<p>Circles? Rectangles? The choice is yours! Most <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/instagram-editing-apps/">Instagram editing tools</a> can help create these unique borders.</p>
<p>Pet food brand <a href="http://instagram.com/iams">@iams</a> did circle frames for its images for a while.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-09.png"><picture decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-400597">
<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-09-310x671.png.webp 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-09-620x1342.png.webp 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-09-768x1662.png.webp 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-09-710x1536.png.webp 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-09-946x2048.png.webp 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-09.png.webp 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
<img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-09-310x671.png" alt="iams pet food brand circular frames on photos" width="310" height="671" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-09-310x671.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-09-620x1342.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-09-768x1662.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-09-710x1536.png 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-09-946x2048.png 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-09.png 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
</picture>
</a></p>
<p>…while charity <a href="http://instagram.com/writers_ex">@writers_ex</a> uses a selection of off-kilter shapes in its signature colors to brand each post.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-10.png"><picture decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-400589">
<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-10-310x671.png.webp 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-10-620x1342.png.webp 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-10-768x1662.png.webp 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-10-710x1536.png.webp 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-10-946x2048.png.webp 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-10.png.webp 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
<img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-10-310x671.png" alt="The Writers&#039; Exchange varying shapes in pictures" width="310" height="671" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-10-310x671.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-10-620x1342.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-10-768x1662.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-10-710x1536.png 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-10-946x2048.png 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-10.png 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
</picture>
</a></p>
<h3><span id="Get_fresh_with_fonts"><a id="post-400341-_4gavxts8bi4z"></a>Get fresh with fonts</span></h3>
<p>Regularly including text in your posts can contribute to a striking, font-forward overall look. There are plenty of accounts out there that specialize in info-images, but even sprinkling in a text-heavy image among the photos can make for a stylish display.</p>
<p>Try thinking about your Instagram grid like the page of a magazine — by strategically scheduling images with words and visuals, you can create a spread with balance that’s full of interesting moments to draw the “reader” in.</p>
<p><a href="http://instagram.com/nikerunning">@nikerunning</a> has a mix of bold text-forward posts, illustrations, and photos, but because they post each of these elements regularly, it feels intentional and cohesive. The lesson? You can have totally disparate ingredients in your design palette, but if you use them regularly and with balance, your grid will look pulled together.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-11.png"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-400581" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-11-310x671.png" alt="Nike Running diverse palette and image selection" width="310" height="671" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-11-310x671.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-11-620x1342.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-11-768x1662.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-11-710x1536.png 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-11-946x2048.png 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-11.png 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"></a></p>
<p>Making a grid that’s all-text-all-the-time works, too. The trick is to stick with a consistent color palette and font selection to make sure each post looks great next to the last, like <a href="http://instagram.com/mr.pugo">@mr.pugo</a> here.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-15.png"><picture decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-400557">
<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-15-310x671.png.webp 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-15-620x1342.png.webp 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-15-768x1662.png.webp 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-15-710x1536.png.webp 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-15-946x2048.png.webp 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-15.png.webp 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
<img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-15-310x671.png" alt="Mr.Pugo Digital Creator text images about color palette and design" width="310" height="671" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-15-310x671.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-15-620x1342.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-15-768x1662.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-15-710x1536.png 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-15-946x2048.png 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-15.png 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
</picture>
</a></p>
<h3><span id="Turn_your_grid_into_the_rainbow"><a id="post-400341-_cplocb3jtw3k"></a><strong>Turn your grid into the rainbow</strong></span></h3>
<p>You need both patience and a great color sense to pull this look off. The goal is to post regularly in one saturated color and slowly transition to the next shade in the rainbow with your next rows of posts.</p>
<p>To truly get the full effect of waterbottle company <a href="http://instagram.com/mybkr">@mybkr</a>’s shifting palette, you’ll need to scroll, but they go through periods of being inspired by the color of one bottle and then move on to another… from sage to baby blue, for example.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-12.png"><picture decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-400573">
<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-12-310x671.png.webp 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-12-620x1342.png.webp 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-12-768x1662.png.webp 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-12-710x1536.png.webp 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-12-946x2048.png.webp 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-12.png.webp 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
<img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-12-310x671.png" alt="mybkr water bottle company varying colour palette" width="310" height="671" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-12-310x671.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-12-620x1342.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-12-768x1662.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-12-710x1536.png 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-12-946x2048.png 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-12.png 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
</picture>
</a></p>
<h3><span id="Embrace_the_border"><a id="post-400341-_i5kdawscw45u"></a><strong>Embrace the border</strong></span></h3>
<p>Creating a consistent look can be as simple as applying a border to all your images.</p>
<p>Influencer <a href="http://instagram.com/kwn.li">@kwn.li</a> uses a white border on all their images, but you could create a signature look with any color scheme. The free <a href="https://apps.apple.com/ca/app/whitagram/id523481129">Whitagram app </a>is one option to quickly apply this edit, with borders and backdrops in all sorts of different shades.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-13.png"><picture decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-400565">
<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-13-310x671.png.webp 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-13-620x1342.png.webp 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-13-768x1662.png.webp 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-13-710x1536.png.webp 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-13-946x2048.png.webp 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-13.png.webp 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
<img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-13-310x671.png" alt="kwn.li influencer photos with white border" width="310" height="671" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-13-310x671.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-13-620x1342.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-13-768x1662.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-13-710x1536.png 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-13-946x2048.png 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-13.png 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
</picture>
</a></p>
<h3><span id="Turn_your_posts_into_a_puzzle"><a id="post-400341-_wyhw864c72ah"></a><strong>Turn your posts into a puzzle</strong></span></h3>
<p>This layout is a tricky one to pull off on a day-to-day basis, but for a big announcement or campaign or to launch a new account, a puzzle grid certainly packs a punch.</p>
<p>A puzzle grid creates one big, interconnected image out of all the squares. Individually, these posts probably look like nonsense. But viewed together, it’s a work of art.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-14.png"><picture decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-400669">
<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-14-310x671.png.webp 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-14-620x1342.png.webp 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-14-768x1662.png.webp 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-14-710x1536.png.webp 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-14-946x2048.png.webp 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-14.png.webp 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
<img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-14-310x671.png" alt="Mamapunt Montessori puzzle grid" width="310" height="671" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-14-310x671.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-14-620x1342.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-14-768x1662.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-14-710x1536.png 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-14-946x2048.png 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-14.png 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
</picture>
</a></p>
<p>Give Montessori account <a href="http://instagram.com/hetmamapunt">@hetmamapunt</a> a round of applause for this visual feat, will ya?</p>
<h3><span id="Consider_a_little_chaos"><a id="post-400341-_p6827y4t96az"></a>Consider a little chaos</span></h3>
<p>In this fast-and-furious social media world, there’s a certain charm to the no-polish-no-worries look.</p>
<p>Adopt the chaotic energy of the “extremely online” set by mashing up memes, screenshots, TikTok reshares, hastily snapped food pics, poorly lit impromptu photo shoots, and whatever else you might find on your camera roll.</p>
<p>Journalist <a href="http://instagram.com/taylorlorenz3.0">Taylor Lorenz</a>’s meme account is a perfect example of this ethos. Think “Explore Page” gone haywire.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-16.jpeg"><picture decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-400549">
<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-16-310x671.jpeg.webp 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-16-620x1342.jpeg.webp 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-16-768x1662.jpeg.webp 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-16-710x1536.jpeg.webp 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-16-946x2048.jpeg.webp 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-16.jpeg.webp 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
<img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-16-310x671.jpeg" alt="Journalist Taylor Lorenz meme account" width="310" height="671" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-16-310x671.jpeg 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-16-620x1342.jpeg 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-16-768x1662.jpeg 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-16-710x1536.jpeg 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-16-946x2048.jpeg 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-16.jpeg 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
</picture>
</a></p>
<p>Viewed as a whole, your grid takes on a trendy <a href="https://www.thecut.com/2022/08/cluttercore-aesthetic-definition.html">cluttercore</a> vibe. If your brand is at one with Gen Z, this unplanned, untamed, wild, and creative Instagram grid style could be for you.</p>
<h2><a id="post-400341-_i0q014yb0l4z"></a><strong>6 tips for planning an Instagram grid</strong></h2>
<p>Of course, none of these sleek grids for Instagram happen by accident. You gotta grind for that grid! Here are some things to keep in mind as you’re planning out the big picture.</p>
<h3><a id="post-400341-_izblbm3nnv0v"></a><strong>1. Preview first</strong></h3>
<p>Before you post it: map it.</p>
<p>You could mock it up in photo-editing software, or use <a href="https://apps.hootsuite.com/apps/instagram-grid">Hootsuite’s app integration</a> that lets you preview your layout before it goes live… think of it as your Instagram grid template.</p>
<p>Right now, it’s for personal accounts only, but business account functionality is coming soon.</p>
<p>Create an Instagram grid layout of up to nine images, and then schedule them to go up in the exact right order <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/how-to-schedule-instagram-posts/">via the Hootsuite dashboard</a>.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-17.png"><picture decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-400541">
<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-17-620x449.png.webp 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-17-310x224.png.webp 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-17-768x556.png.webp 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-17-1536x1112.png.webp 1536w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-17.png.webp 1768w" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px"/>
<img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-17-620x449.png" alt="create Instagram grid layout using Hootsuite" width="620" height="449" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-17-620x449.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-17-310x224.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-17-768x556.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-17-1536x1112.png 1536w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-17.png 1768w" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px"/>
</picture>
</a></p>
<h3><a id="post-400341-_utm462cazhet"></a><strong>2. Keep it consistent</strong></h3>
<p>Creating a great Instagram photo grid means sticking to a plan. One off-beat photo in the wrong color, the wrong filter, or in the wrong order can throw your whole look out of whack.</p>
<p>Just imagine if makeup company <a href="http://instagram.com/bareminerals">@bareminerals</a> tossed in a picture of a night at a neon-tinged rave to their earthy skin-toned, carefully curated grid. Chaos!</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-18.png"><picture decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-400533">
<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-18-310x671.png.webp 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-18-620x1342.png.webp 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-18-768x1662.png.webp 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-18-710x1536.png.webp 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-18-946x2048.png.webp 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-18.png.webp 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
<img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-18-310x671.png" alt="Bare Minerals makeup earth tone grid" width="310" height="671" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-18-310x671.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-18-620x1342.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-18-768x1662.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-18-710x1536.png 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-18-946x2048.png 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-18.png 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
</picture>
</a></p>
<h3><a id="post-400341-_5781e03e8zl2"></a><strong>3. Make sure it matches your brand</strong></h3>
<p>Ultimately, the goal of a grid isn’t just to impress your friends with your dedication to using a <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/free-instagram-presets/">particular Lightroom preset</a> filter. It’s to build a unified look for your brand.</p>
<p>So, if you’re a recruiting firm for high-level executives, having a playful rainbow grid might not quite fit the professional and serious tone you’re going for. A monochromatic, text-based series of posts, on the other hand…</p>
<h3><a id="post-400341-_lh8701uqc0zh"></a><strong>4. Take advantage of image editing tools</strong></h3>
<p>In case you haven’t figured it out yet: Instagram is a visual medium… and it’s hard to put together a great grid unless the individual pictures <em>also </em>are great.</p>
<p>Luckily, there are tons of great <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/resources-to-create-quick-and-beautiful-images-for-social-media/">photo editing tools</a> out there, as well as expert advice around every corner… for example, our guides to <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/how-to-take-good-instagram-photos/">taking great Instagram photos</a> and<a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/instagram-photo-editing-trends/"> staying on top of the hottest Instagram trends</a>.</p>
<h3><a id="post-400341-_d44szz1yfpqu"></a>5. Don’t forget: Reels are part of your grid, too</h3>
<p>Your Instagram Reels can live on your grid alongside your main posts, so don’t forget to select a suitable <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/instagram-reels-cover/">Reels cover photo.</a> Or use one of our professionally-designed <a href="https://www.hootsuite.com/resources/blog/instagram-reel-cover-templates">Reels Cover Templates</a> to create a consistent look for your Reels.</p>
<p>Each of <a href="http://instagram.com/airbnb">@airbnb</a>’s Reels have a carefully selected cover photo of a rental home, viewed from a street-level exterior. It creates a sense of consistency with your other Instagram grid posts.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-19.png"><picture decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-400525">
<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-19-310x671.png.webp 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-19-620x1342.png.webp 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-19-768x1662.png.webp 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-19-710x1536.png.webp 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-19-946x2048.png.webp 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-19.png.webp 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
<img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-19-310x671.png" alt="Airbnb Reels rental home cover photos" width="310" height="671" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-19-310x671.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-19-620x1342.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-19-768x1662.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-19-710x1536.png 710w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-19-946x2048.png 946w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/instagram-grid-19.png 1170w" sizes="(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px"/>
</picture>
</a></p>
<h3><a id="post-400341-_fmr1yeqyc8ma"></a>6<strong>. Schedule your posts in advance</strong></h3>
<p>Keep your gorgeous IG grid active and updated with the help of a scheduling tool that allows you to drop just the right filtered pic (or three) at just the right time. <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/how-to-schedule-instagram-posts/">Hootsuite’s dashboard</a>, for example, makes it easy to prep your best photos at your convenience. Get that grid going!</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone wp-image-416307 size-full" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/visual-planner.gif" alt="Hootsuite Visual Planner" width="512" height="332"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="hs-btn hs-btn-green" href="https://www.hootsuite.com/select-plan">Try Hootsuite for $0</a></p>
<p>Of course, creating a great grid is just one way to capture attention on the ‘gram. For more marketing tips and tricks to take your account to the next level, <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/instagram-marketing/">check out our ultimate guide to Instagram marketing here</a>.</p>
<h2><a id="post-400341-_j0ibuupc1553"></a><strong>Instagram grid FAQs</strong></h2>
<h3><span id="How_do_you_post_a_33_grid_on_Instagram"><a id="post-400341-_5ap003z03a1e"></a><strong>How do you post a 3×3 grid on Instagram?</strong></span></h3>
<p>If you want to do a grid layout on Instagram, you’re going to need to do some pre-planning.</p>
<p>Mock it up in photo-editing software, or use <a href="https://apps.hootsuite.com/apps/instagram-grid">Hootsuite’s Instagram Grid planner integration</a> to preview your layout before it goes live.</p>
<p>(Note: right now, it’s for personal accounts only, but business account functionality is coming soon.)</p>
<p>Create an Instagram grid layout of up to nine images, and then schedule them to go up in the exact right order <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/how-to-schedule-instagram-posts/">via the Hootsuite dashboard</a>.</p>
<h3><a id="post-400341-_4x4q3zfbby9b"></a><strong>How do I change my grid on Instagram?</strong></h3>
<p>Changing your grid on Instagram starts with deciding on your new look. Do you want the posts to all be in a specific, consistent color palette? Should each image on the grid contribute to one big picture? What is your visual goal and how does it tie in to your Instagram brand?</p>
<p>Peep some of our creative inspiration sources above to figure out what you want your Instagram account to look like, or explore <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/instagram-photo-editing-trends/">2023’s biggest Instagram photo-editing trends</a> to spark some ideas for your big grid makeover.</p>
<p>Before you start adding your new images, delete or archive anything that you’ve previously posted that doesn’t match your desired look.</p>
<p>Now it’s time to start plotting out your fresh content.</p>
<p>Either mock it up in photo-editing software or use <a href="https://apps.hootsuite.com/apps/instagram-grid">Hootsuite’s Instagram Grid planner integration</a> to preview your layout before it goes live. (Use these <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/how-to-edit-instagram-photos/">Instagram editing tips</a> to give your images a consistent aesthetic.)</p>
<p>Create an Instagram grid layout of up to nine images, and then schedule them to go up in the exact right order <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/how-to-schedule-instagram-posts/">via the Hootsuite dashboard</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Start building your Instagram presence using Hootsuite. Schedule and publish posts directly to Instagram, engage your audience, measure performance, and run all your other social media profiles — all from one simple dashboard. Try it free today.</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="btn btn--secondary" href="https://www.hootsuite.com/select-plan">Get Started</a></p>
